[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":677},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fjsweirdworld-22-objects-and-the-dot\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fjsweirdworld-22-objects-and-the-dot\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fjsweirdworld-22-objects-and-the-dot\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fjsweirdworld-22-objects-and-the-dot\u002F":652,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fjsweirdworld-22-objects-and-the-dot\u002F":661},"\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F20190517\u002F4033482277\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":634,"date":635,"description":636,"extension":637,"lang":638,"meta":639,"navigation":640,"path":641,"readingMinutes":642,"seo":643,"standalone":644,"stem":645,"tags":646,"tldr":649,"updated":635,"url":650,"__hash__":651},"content\u002Fen\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjsweirdworld-22-objects-and-the-dot.md","[JS Weird World] No.22 Objects and the Dot Operator","1000110869",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":629},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,37,42,45,81,88,130,137,225,230,233,311,317,328,392,395,401,404,410,413,482,489,492,568,574,591,606,612,616,625],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"We're kicking off a new chapter here: objects and functions. A lot of courses teach these two as completely separate topics, and honestly that's a huge mistake. In most other languages they really are separate things, but in the JavaScript world they're tightly connected.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"objects-and-the-dot","Objects and the Dot",[17,25,26],{},"We talked about objects in an earlier chapter — an object is a collection of name\u002Fvalue pairs, like this:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"object","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FR6q5QAb.png",[17,35,36],{},"To make things easier to explain, let's look at objects from a slightly different angle. An object can usually hold values, other objects, and functions, like this:",[17,38,39],{},[30,40],{"alt":32,"src":41},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FtMzl2ae.png",[17,43,44],{},"A function that lives inside an object is usually called a method. So how does an object actually find a function, an object, or a value inside it? Let's look at an example.",[46,47,52],"pre",{"className":48,"code":49,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","var person = new Object();\n","js","",[53,54,55],"code",{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,57,60,64,68,71,74,78],"span",{"class":58,"line":59},"line",1,[56,61,63],{"class":62},"sWyjQ","var",[56,65,67],{"class":66},"sMAXC"," person ",[56,69,70],{"class":62},"=",[56,72,73],{"class":62}," new",[56,75,77],{"class":76},"sj_SG"," Object",[56,79,80],{"class":66},"();\n",[17,82,83,84,87],{},"The course starts by using ",[53,85,86],{},"new"," to create a new object. At that point memory knows it's an object. So how do we write data into it? With the bracket operator:",[46,89,91],{"className":48,"code":90,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"person['fistname'] = 'Tony';\nperson['lastname'] = 'Alicea';\n",[53,92,93,113],{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,94,95,98,102,105,107,110],{"class":58,"line":59},[56,96,97],{"class":66},"person[",[56,99,101],{"class":100},"sTRMh","'fistname'",[56,103,104],{"class":66},"] ",[56,106,70],{"class":62},[56,108,109],{"class":100}," 'Tony'",[56,111,112],{"class":66},";\n",[56,114,116,118,121,123,125,128],{"class":58,"line":115},2,[56,117,97],{"class":66},[56,119,120],{"class":100},"'lastname'",[56,122,104],{"class":66},[56,124,70],{"class":62},[56,126,127],{"class":100}," 'Alicea'",[56,129,112],{"class":66},[17,131,132,133,136],{},"Writing it this way lets the object reference its spot in memory and store the value. Now let's try logging out ",[53,134,135],{},"person",":",[46,138,140],{"className":48,"code":139,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = new Object();\nperson['fistname'] = 'Tony';\nperson['lastname'] = 'Alicea';\nconsole.log(person);\nconsole.log(person['fistname']);\nconsole.log(person['lastname']);\n",[53,141,142,156,170,185,197,212],{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,143,144,146,148,150,152,154],{"class":58,"line":59},[56,145,63],{"class":62},[56,147,67],{"class":66},[56,149,70],{"class":62},[56,151,73],{"class":62},[56,153,77],{"class":76},[56,155,80],{"class":66},[56,157,158,160,162,164,166,168],{"class":58,"line":115},[56,159,97],{"class":66},[56,161,101],{"class":100},[56,163,104],{"class":66},[56,165,70],{"class":62},[56,167,109],{"class":100},[56,169,112],{"class":66},[56,171,173,175,177,179,181,183],{"class":58,"line":172},3,[56,174,97],{"class":66},[56,176,120],{"class":100},[56,178,104],{"class":66},[56,180,70],{"class":62},[56,182,127],{"class":100},[56,184,112],{"class":66},[56,186,188,191,194],{"class":58,"line":187},4,[56,189,190],{"class":66},"console.",[56,192,193],{"class":76},"log",[56,195,196],{"class":66},"(person);\n",[56,198,200,202,204,207,209],{"class":58,"line":199},5,[56,201,190],{"class":66},[56,203,193],{"class":76},[56,205,206],{"class":66},"(person[",[56,208,101],{"class":100},[56,210,211],{"class":66},"]);\n",[56,213,215,217,219,221,223],{"class":58,"line":214},6,[56,216,190],{"class":66},[56,218,193],{"class":76},[56,220,206],{"class":66},[56,222,120],{"class":100},[56,224,211],{"class":66},[17,226,227],{},[30,228],{"alt":135,"src":229},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F5twGUDA.png",[17,231,232],{},"You can also grab the object's data through a variable:",[46,234,236],{"className":48,"code":235,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = new Object();\nperson['fistname'] = 'Tony';\nperson['lastname'] = 'Alicea';\nvar firstNamePropety = 'fistname';\nconsole.log(person);\nconsole.log(person[firstNamePropety]);\n",[53,237,238,252,266,280,294,302],{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,239,240,242,244,246,248,250],{"class":58,"line":59},[56,241,63],{"class":62},[56,243,67],{"class":66},[56,245,70],{"class":62},[56,247,73],{"class":62},[56,249,77],{"class":76},[56,251,80],{"class":66},[56,253,254,256,258,260,262,264],{"class":58,"line":115},[56,255,97],{"class":66},[56,257,101],{"class":100},[56,259,104],{"class":66},[56,261,70],{"class":62},[56,263,109],{"class":100},[56,265,112],{"class":66},[56,267,268,270,272,274,276,278],{"class":58,"line":172},[56,269,97],{"class":66},[56,271,120],{"class":100},[56,273,104],{"class":66},[56,275,70],{"class":62},[56,277,127],{"class":100},[56,279,112],{"class":66},[56,281,282,284,287,289,292],{"class":58,"line":187},[56,283,63],{"class":62},[56,285,286],{"class":66}," firstNamePropety ",[56,288,70],{"class":62},[56,290,291],{"class":100}," 'fistname'",[56,293,112],{"class":66},[56,295,296,298,300],{"class":58,"line":199},[56,297,190],{"class":66},[56,299,193],{"class":76},[56,301,196],{"class":66},[56,303,304,306,308],{"class":58,"line":214},[56,305,190],{"class":66},[56,307,193],{"class":76},[56,309,310],{"class":66},"(person[firstNamePropety]);\n",[17,312,313],{},[30,314],{"alt":315,"src":316},"getting a value through a variable","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLpkyN8T.png",[17,318,319,320,323,324,136],{},"The result is the same as ",[53,321,322],{},"console.log(person['fistname']);",". And there's yet another way to pull values out of an object — the ",[325,326,327],"strong",{},"dot (.) operator",[46,329,331],{"className":48,"code":330,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = new Object();\nperson['fistname'] = 'Tony';\nperson['lastname'] = 'Alicea';\nconsole.log(person);\nconsole.log(person.fistname);\n",[53,332,333,347,361,375,383],{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,334,335,337,339,341,343,345],{"class":58,"line":59},[56,336,63],{"class":62},[56,338,67],{"class":66},[56,340,70],{"class":62},[56,342,73],{"class":62},[56,344,77],{"class":76},[56,346,80],{"class":66},[56,348,349,351,353,355,357,359],{"class":58,"line":115},[56,350,97],{"class":66},[56,352,101],{"class":100},[56,354,104],{"class":66},[56,356,70],{"class":62},[56,358,109],{"class":100},[56,360,112],{"class":66},[56,362,363,365,367,369,371,373],{"class":58,"line":172},[56,364,97],{"class":66},[56,366,120],{"class":100},[56,368,104],{"class":66},[56,370,70],{"class":62},[56,372,127],{"class":100},[56,374,112],{"class":66},[56,376,377,379,381],{"class":58,"line":187},[56,378,190],{"class":66},[56,380,193],{"class":76},[56,382,196],{"class":66},[56,384,385,387,389],{"class":58,"line":199},[56,386,190],{"class":66},[56,388,193],{"class":76},[56,390,391],{"class":66},"(person.fistname);\n",[17,393,394],{},"One thing to note here: the dot (.) operator is also a function.",[17,396,397],{},[30,398],{"alt":399,"src":400},"dot operator","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbsoviPy.png",[17,402,403],{},"The MDN docs even point out that the dot operator's precedence is the second highest!",[17,405,406],{},[30,407],{"alt":408,"src":409},"MDN","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLw7oxxG.png",[17,411,412],{},"So what the dot operator is really doing looks like this. The mechanics here come down to the syntax parser — the moment it reads the dot operator, it knows to do this conversion:",[46,414,416],{"className":48,"code":415,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = new Object();\nperson['fistname'] = 'Tony';\nperson['lastname'] = 'Alicea';\nconsole.log(person);\nconsole.log(person.'fistname');\n",[53,417,418,432,446,460,468],{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,419,420,422,424,426,428,430],{"class":58,"line":59},[56,421,63],{"class":62},[56,423,67],{"class":66},[56,425,70],{"class":62},[56,427,73],{"class":62},[56,429,77],{"class":76},[56,431,80],{"class":66},[56,433,434,436,438,440,442,444],{"class":58,"line":115},[56,435,97],{"class":66},[56,437,101],{"class":100},[56,439,104],{"class":66},[56,441,70],{"class":62},[56,443,109],{"class":100},[56,445,112],{"class":66},[56,447,448,450,452,454,456,458],{"class":58,"line":172},[56,449,97],{"class":66},[56,451,120],{"class":100},[56,453,104],{"class":66},[56,455,70],{"class":62},[56,457,127],{"class":100},[56,459,112],{"class":66},[56,461,462,464,466],{"class":58,"line":187},[56,463,190],{"class":66},[56,465,193],{"class":76},[56,467,196],{"class":66},[56,469,470,472,474,477,479],{"class":58,"line":199},[56,471,190],{"class":66},[56,473,193],{"class":76},[56,475,476],{"class":66},"(person.",[56,478,101],{"class":100},[56,480,481],{"class":66},");\n",[17,483,484,485,488],{},"The course mentions there's a proper term for this: it's called the ",[325,486,487],{},"member access"," operator, and the \"member\" is a member of the object.",[17,490,491],{},"The course also does this — creating an object inside another object:",[46,493,495],{"className":48,"code":494,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = new Object();\nperson['fistname'] = 'Tony';\nperson['lastname'] = 'Alicea';\nconsole.log(person);\nconsole.log(person.fistname);\nperson.address = new Object();\n",[53,496,497,511,525,539,547,555],{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,498,499,501,503,505,507,509],{"class":58,"line":59},[56,500,63],{"class":62},[56,502,67],{"class":66},[56,504,70],{"class":62},[56,506,73],{"class":62},[56,508,77],{"class":76},[56,510,80],{"class":66},[56,512,513,515,517,519,521,523],{"class":58,"line":115},[56,514,97],{"class":66},[56,516,101],{"class":100},[56,518,104],{"class":66},[56,520,70],{"class":62},[56,522,109],{"class":100},[56,524,112],{"class":66},[56,526,527,529,531,533,535,537],{"class":58,"line":172},[56,528,97],{"class":66},[56,530,120],{"class":100},[56,532,104],{"class":66},[56,534,70],{"class":62},[56,536,127],{"class":100},[56,538,112],{"class":66},[56,540,541,543,545],{"class":58,"line":187},[56,542,190],{"class":66},[56,544,193],{"class":76},[56,546,196],{"class":66},[56,548,549,551,553],{"class":58,"line":199},[56,550,190],{"class":66},[56,552,193],{"class":76},[56,554,391],{"class":66},[56,556,557,560,562,564,566],{"class":58,"line":214},[56,558,559],{"class":66},"person.address ",[56,561,70],{"class":62},[56,563,73],{"class":62},[56,565,77],{"class":76},[56,567,80],{"class":66},[17,569,570,571,573],{},"And then you can use the ",[325,572,399],{}," to add properties and values:",[46,575,577],{"className":48,"code":576,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"person.address.street = '111 Main';\n",[53,578,579],{"__ignoreMap":51},[56,580,581,584,586,589],{"class":58,"line":59},[56,582,583],{"class":66},"person.address.street ",[56,585,70],{"class":62},[56,587,588],{"class":100}," '111 Main'",[56,590,112],{"class":66},[17,592,593,594,597,598,601,602,605],{},"When operators have the same precedence, what matters next is associativity. The course explains that the ",[325,595,596],{},"dot operator is left-associative",", so it goes from left (",[53,599,600],{},"address",") to right (",[53,603,604],{},"street",").",[607,608,609],"blockquote",{},[17,610,611],{},"An object is just a collection of name\u002Fvalue pairs, and inside it you can have strings, booleans, functions, and so on.",[12,613,615],{"id":614},"image-source","Image Source",[17,617,618],{},[619,620,624],"a",{"href":621,"rel":622},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.udemy.com\u002Fjavascriptjs\u002F",[623],"nofollow","JavaScript: Understanding the Weird Parts",[626,627,628],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}",{"title":51,"searchDepth":115,"dept